The paper discusses a cryptographic scheme based on chaotic systems, which is a common topic in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of pseudorandom bit padding and image algorithms suggests a potential connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia), respectively. The paper also mentions the evaluation of the scheme's security through key space analysis and differential attack, which are techniques commonly used in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of image encryption suggests a potential connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
